<task id="task_1A701C1D041F46228299B24C694B3E23">
  <title>Add the AppMeasurement for Flash Library to a Project</title>
  <shortdesc>The Flash media module provides the interface to track video. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <keyword>media</keyword>
        <keyword>milestone</keyword>
        <keyword>sdk</keyword>
        <keyword>video</keyword>
      </keywords>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Developer and implementation" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <steps id="steps_4A22529C75514B49AEEB319FFF041F9C">
      <step id="step_95E22D3045C34B68BB8B45B2A0A467CD">
        <cmd>Launch Flash Professional and open the Flash project where you
			 want to include a Flash video. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <?xm-replace_text Step Result?>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_84A27322F5ED4C17953C60FA98DA868A">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>File</uicontrol> &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>Publish Settings</uicontrol>, and then open 
			 <uicontrol>ActionScript Settings</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <image placement="break" align="center" href="graphics/video-flash-publish-settings.png" width="500px" id="image_3D05606D5DC14E9EBE3ADA7238D1BBF8"></image>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_9BB939315B7749E8ADE1F370DD0C9AA9">
        <cmd>Add the 
			 <codeph>AppMeasurement.swc</codeph> library to your project. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <image placement="break" align="center" href="graphics/video-flash-library-path.png" id="image_39F884C0ADA14D6C904796BF366EB35A"></image>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_33EC20D69252478C843EA4B3DB1AB06A">
        <cmd>In the 
			 <uicontrol>Timeline</uicontrol> pane, select a frame that is
			 available to the entire Flash application and open 
			 <uicontrol>Actions</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_0ABCC936FAE64E1099228DABBEA981AB">
        <cmd>To test that the library was added successfully, add the following
			 ActionScript code to the Actions: 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <codeblock>import com.omniture.AppMeasurement;

var s:AppMeasurement = new AppMeasurement();
s.account</codeblock>
          <p>As you type "<codeph>s.account</codeph>", auto complete should
				appear. This indicates that the library is being found successfully. 
			 </p>
          <image placement="break" align="center" href="graphics/video-flash-verify-library.png" id="image_92163C2649914E8C850151348768D22D"></image>
          <p>Take a quick look at the methods and variables in the 
				<codeph>Media</codeph> namespace, since that is where you'll spend
				most of your time as you configure video: 
			 </p>
          <image placement="break" align="center" href="graphics/video-flash-verify-library-media.png" id="image_5DF5AA0A799A4388BD9743A4716D536E"></image>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <example id="example_195A4458BAFF4433A29CEBF6B41F9308">
      <p>
        <b>Next step:</b>
        <xref href="video_flash_config_core.xml#task_1D29FC9D72AB4D53A703230FE4D9FEAB" format="dita" scope="local">
          <?xm-replace_text Configure AppMeasurement?>
        </xref>.
		  
		</p>
    </example>
  </taskbody>
</task>